{#- TL;DR (body) — "In one paragraph". -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbcon-tldr" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">QuickBooks consulting, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>QuickBooks consulting is an ongoing advisory retainer &mdash; not a one-time project, not support tickets, not training. A Certified ProAdvisor is embedded in your QuickBooks workflow to optimize configuration as the business grows, catch problems before they compound, troubleshoot integration failures when connected apps drift, build and maintain the custom reports leadership actually uses, and answer QuickBooks questions with expert judgment rather than generic support responses. The engagement covers workflow optimization (identifying where QuickBooks adds friction instead of reducing it); configuration audits (reviewing accumulated drift, ad-hoc changes, and inefficiencies); integration management (Shopify, Stripe, Bill.com, Gusto, industry-specific apps); custom reporting (class reports, location P&amp;Ls, KPI dashboards inside QuickBooks); payroll configuration support (not payroll processing &mdash; configuration and advisory); and direct ProAdvisor access for questions as they arise.</p>
      <p>Pricing is a monthly retainer, typically $500&ndash;$1,500/month for simpler QuickBooks Online businesses; $1,500&ndash;$3,500/month for Enterprise or high-integration complexity. An initial configuration audit at engagement start establishes baseline. It&rsquo;s not the right engagement for one-time error fixes (see <a href="/quickbooks/help/error-codes/">error code references</a>), initial setup (see <a href="/quickbooks/setup/">QuickBooks setup</a>), or payroll processing (see <a href="/quickbooks/payroll/">payroll services</a>). It coordinates with your CPA on tax matters; it doesn&rsquo;t include tax filing, IRS representation, audit, or assurance. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- DRIFT — the problem consulting solves → r-3 dc-card. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbcon-drift">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The problem consulting solves</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">QuickBooks configurations drift. Most businesses don&rsquo;t know until it&rsquo;s expensive.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Configuration drift is gradual and invisible until it isn&rsquo;t. Six patterns that signal a configuration that&rsquo;s fallen behind the business.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for d in drift %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ d.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- COVERS — six advisory areas → r-3 dc-card. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbcon-covers" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What the engagement covers</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Six advisory areas, one ongoing retainer.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">The retainer scope is defined at engagement start and adjusted as the business evolves. The six areas below cover the most common consulting work; the actual mix depends on the business.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for c in covers %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ c.num }}</span><h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ c.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- PRICING — monthly retainer tiers → .ptier r-3. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbcon-pricing">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Pricing</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Monthly retainer, scoped by complexity.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:72ch;">Retainer pricing scales with QuickBooks product, business complexity, integration count, and advisory scope. Every engagement starts with a configuration audit to establish baseline and set retainer scope.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for p in pricing %}
      <div class="ptier">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ p.tier | safe }}</span>
        <h3>{{ p.price | safe }}</h3>
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin:4px 0 12px;">{{ p.cadence | safe }}</span>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:0 0 10px;"><strong>Fits:</strong> {{ p.fit | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          {%- for li in p.includes %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:20px;max-width:72ch;">All retainers include an initial configuration audit before ongoing advisory begins. Minimum engagement period applies; retainer scope reviewed quarterly and adjusted as the business evolves. No hourly billing outside the retainer.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- VERSUS — consulting vs other QB engagements → r-3 dc-card. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbcon-versus" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
